        <mxCell id="cross" value="&lt;b&gt;Cross-cutting&lt;/b&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;Microsoft Purview (unified lineage)&#160;&#183;&#160;Azure Key Vault (CMK + secrets via RBAC)&#160;&#183;&#160;Application Insights / Azure Monitor (telemetry, drift, alerts)" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#E1D5E7;strokeColor=#9673A6;fontSize=12;align=center;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="100" y="640" width="1400" height="50" as="geometry"/>
        </mxCell>

        <mxCell id="legend" value="" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#999999;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="100" y="710" width="1400" height="220" as="geometry"/>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="leg_title" value="&lt;b&gt;What this picture says (and what it does not)&lt;/b&gt;" style="text;html=1;fontSize=13;fontStyle=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="120" y="720" width="500" height="24" as="geometry"/>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="leg_says" value="&lt;b&gt;Says.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&#8226; ADLS Gen2 is the single physical contract.&lt;br/&gt;&#8226; Fabric and Azure ML each see it through their own native object (shortcut / datastore).&lt;br/&gt;&#8226; Identity is Entra everywhere; secrets live in Key Vault; lineage is unified in Purview.&lt;br/&gt;&#8226; Predictions land back on the same ADLS Gen2 and reappear in Fabric via the shortcut." style="text;html=1;fontSize=11;align=left;verticalAlign=top;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="120" y="746" width="680" height="170" as="geometry"/>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="leg_doesnot" value="&lt;b&gt;Does not say.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&#8226; That Azure ML reads OneLake directly &#8212; Microsoft documents that this is &lt;i&gt;not&lt;/i&gt; supported. Use the shared ADLS Gen2 instead.&lt;br/&gt;&#8226; That the data is replicated. Same bytes, two logical paths.&lt;br/&gt;&#8226; That the choice between Fabric notebook and Azure ML Studio matters for the artifacts. Both produce the same FeatureSet in the same store. They are complementary entry points." style="text;html=1;fontSize=11;align=left;verticalAlign=top;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="820" y="746" width="660" height="170" as="geometry"/>
        </mxCell>

        <mxCell id="e_entra_fab" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=1;html=1;dashed=1;strokeColor=#1F2D54;strokeWidth=1;endArrow=open;" edge="1" parent="1" source="entra" target="fab">
